    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#26019\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">admirable</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adj.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>15世纪中期，“值得钦佩的”，源自拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">admirabilis</i> “令人钦佩的，奇妙的”，来自 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">admirari</i> “钦佩”（参见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of admire \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/admire\">admire</a>）。在早期，它还带有更强烈的“令人敬畏的，奇妙的”意义。</p>"
    }
  ],
  "relate": [
    {
      "title": "admire<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(v.)</div>",
      "html": "<p>15世纪初（隐含在 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">admired</i> 中），“惊奇地看待，惊叹”，源自古法语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">admirer</i> “看待，沉思”（更正自14世纪的 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">amirer</i>），或直接源自拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">admirari</i> “惊奇地看待，感到惊讶”，由 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ad</i> “关于，关于”（参见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ad- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/ad-\">ad-</a>)和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">mirari</i> “惊奇”，源自 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">mirus</i> “奇妙的”（参见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of smile \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/smile\">smile</a>（v.））。这个意义逐渐减弱，变成“以愉悦和尊敬的态度看待”，但有一段时间它们是重叠的。</p><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground text-content4-foreground\">Doe not admire why I admire :</blockquote><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground text-content4-foreground\">My fever is no other's fire :</blockquote><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground text-content4-foreground\">Each severall heart hath his desire ;</blockquote><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground text-content4-foreground\">Els proof is false, and truth a lier.</blockquote><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground text-content4-foreground mb-2\">[Campion, \"And would You Faine the Reason Knowe,\" in \"Rosseter's Booke of Ayres Part II,\" 1601]</blockquote><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground\">不要惊讶我为什么惊讶：</blockquote><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground\">我的热情不是别人的火焰：</blockquote><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground\">每个人的心都有自己的欲望； </blockquote><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground\">否则，证明是假的，真理是谎言。</blockquote><blockquote class=\"not-italic my-0 text-content1-foreground\">[坎皮恩，“你想知道原因吗”，收录于“罗塞特的艾尔斯第二部分”，1601年]</blockquote><p>相关： <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Admiring</i>； <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">admiringly</i>。</p>"
    },
    {
      "title": "admirably<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adv.)</div>",
      "html": "<p>\"以一种激起赞赏和尊敬的方式\"，来自1590年代的 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of admirable \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/admirable\">admirable</a> + <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of -ly \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/-ly#etymonline_v_32027\">-ly</a> (2)。</p>"
    }
